o\": 1208}, {\"ngram\": \"raucous boos\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1226}, {\"ngram\": \".08 seconds\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1242}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Andre de Grasse of Canada took the bronze.\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1286, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1244, \"end\": 1259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andre_De_Grasse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andre de Grasse\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andre_De_Grasse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andre_De_Grasse\"}, {\"begin\": 1263, \"end\": 1269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.983829983270699, \"rank\": 0.014856015989520027, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the bronze\", \"from\": 1275, \"to\": 1285}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bolt has a chance for two more golds - in his favorite race, Thursday's 200 final, where he has pronounced he will be gunning for the world record, then the 4x100 relay Saturday night.\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1472, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bolt\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1292}, {\"ngram\": \"a chance\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1305}, {\"ngram\": \"two more golds\", \"from\": 1310, \"to\": 1324}, {\"ngram\": \"his favorite race\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1347}, {\"ngram\": \"the world record\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1434}, {\"ngram\": \"then the 4x100 relay\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1456}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking of world records - a few minutes before Bolt's race, world champion Wayde van Niekerk of South Africa eclipsed what many thought was the most-unbreakable mark in the book - Michael Johnson's 17-year-old run of 43.18 seconds in 400 meters.\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1721, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1551, \"end\": 1568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wayde van Niekerk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\"}, {\"begin\": 1572, \"end\": 1584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.891995829446996, \"rank\": 0.12108146745914965, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 1656, \"end\": 1671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Johnson_(sprinter)\", \"score\": 0.6562406956371172, \"rank\": 0.27532889874358996, \"text\": \"Michael Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Johnson_(sprinter)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Johnson_(sprinter)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"world records\", \"from\": 1486, \"to\": 1499}, {\"ngram\": \"Bolt's race\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1534}, {\"ngram\": \"the most-unbreakable mark\", \"from\": 1616, \"to\": 1641}, {\"ngram\": \"43.18 seconds\", \"from\": 1693, \"to\": 1706}, {\"ngram\": \"400 meters\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1720}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Running out of Lane 8, where the lag puts him well in front of the rest of the field, van Niekerk never saw a soul - crossing in 43.03 and only glancing to his left when he approached the line to peer at the clock, which showed him what he had done.\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1972, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Lane\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1742}, {\"ngram\": \"the lag\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1759}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1782}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 1786, \"to\": 1794}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 1807}, {\"ngram\": \"van Niekerk\", \"from\": 1809, \"to\": 1820}, {\"ngram\": \"his left\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 1887}, {\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 1907, \"to\": 1915}, {\"ngram\": \"the clock\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1936}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Usain Bolt will be retiring soon, but this could be the next star of the sport,\\\" Johnson said during his commentary on BBC.\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 2100, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2058, \"end\": 2065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randy_Johnson\", \"score\": 0.9998930372650825, \"rank\": 0.00010672104658837633, \"text\": \"Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randy_Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randy_Johnson\"}, {\"begin\": 2096, \"end\": 2099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.6543282869289014, \"rank\": 0.528284479233913, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Usain Bolt\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 1987}, {\"ngram\": \"the next star\", \"from\": 2029, \"to\": 2042}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 2046, \"to\": 2055}, {\"ngram\": \"his commentary\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2092}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Bolt is not done quite yet.\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2135, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bolt\", \"from\": 2108, \"to\": 2112}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 6-foot-5 sprinter/celebrity overcame his typically slow unfurling from the blocks - he was second-to-last after the break.\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2265, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 6-foot-5 sprinter/celebrity\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2170}, {\"ngram\": \"his typically slow unfurling\", \"from\": 2180, \"to\": 2208}, {\"ngram\": \"the blocks\", \"from\": 2214, \"to\": 2224}, {\"ngram\": \"the break\", \"from\": 2255, \"to\": 2264}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I just said, 'Take your time, and chip away,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2269, \"to\": 2324, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your time\", \"from\": 2289, \"to\": 2298}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Churning his legs to gradually build up speed, he eventually caught Gatlin with about 40 meters left and took it to warp speed.\", \"from\": 2328, \"to\": 2455, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his legs\", \"from\": 2337, \"to\": 2345}, {\"ngram\": \"speed\", \"from\": 2368, \"to\": 2373}, {\"ngram\": \"Gatlin\", \"from\": 2396, \"to\": 2402}, {\"ngram\": \"about 40 meters\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2423}, {\"ngram\": \"speed\", \"from\": 2449, \"to\": 2454}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rest was a matter of how hard he wanted to run to the line.\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2519, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The rest\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2464}, {\"ngram\": \"a matter\", \"from\": 2469, \"to\": 2477}, {\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 2510, \"to\": 2518}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"From the start, really,\\\" Bolt said, when asked when he knew he was going to win.\", \"from\": 2523, \"to\": 2604, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 2529, \"to\": 2538}, {\"ngram\": \"Bolt\", \"from\": 2549, \"to\": 2553}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When I got going, got to about 50 meters, I was all right.\", \"from\": 2605, \"to\": 2664, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"about 50 meters\", \"from\": 2631, \"to\": 2646}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I could tell I was going to catch him.\\\"\", \"from\": 2665, \"to\": 2704, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gatlin made Bolt work for it, the way he has for the past four years.\", \"from\": 2708, \"to\": 2777, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gatlin\", \"from\": 2708, \"to\": 2714}, {\"ngram\": \"Bolt\", \"from\": 2720, \"to\": 2724}, {\"ngram\": \"the past four years\", \"from\": 2757, \"to\": 2776}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said the short turnaround between the semifinal and final sapped his strength, and Bolt agreed.\", \"from\": 2778, \"to\": 2876, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the short turnaround\", \"from\": 2786, \"to\": 2806}, {\"ngram\": \"his strength\", \"from\": 2846, \"to\": 2858}, {\"ngram\": \"Bolt\", \"from\": 2864, \"to\": 2868}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"First time we have had to jog to the warmup area to get ready for the final,\\\" Bolt said.\", \"from\": 2880, \"to\": 2969, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the warmup area\", \"from\": 2914, \"to\": 2929}, {\"ngram\": \"Bolt\", \"from\": 2959, \"to\": 2963}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gatlin finished with silver to go with his 2004 gold and 2102 bronze and, at 34, became the oldest man to win a medal in a non-relay sprint.\", \"from\": 2973, \"to\": 3113, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gatlin\", \"from\": 2973, \"to\": 2979}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 2994, \"to\": 3000}, {\"ngram\": \"his 2004 gold\", \"from\": 3012, \"to\": 3025}, {\"ngram\": \"2102 bronze\", \"from\": 3030, \"to\": 3041}, {\"ngram\": \"the oldest man\", \"from\": 3061, \"to\": 3075}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 3083, \"to\": 3090}, {\"ngram\": \"a non-relay sprint\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3112}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And while Bolt was celebrating with anyone he could find, Gatlin was parading the American flag around the track virtually alone.\", \"from\": 3117, \"to\": 3246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3199, \"end\": 3212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.03678839075807e-21, \"text\": \"American flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bolt\", \"from\": 3127, \"to\": 3131}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 3153, \"to\": 3159}, {\"ngram\": \"Gatlin\", \"from\": 3175, \"to\": 3181}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 3220, \"to\": 3229}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The boos from the Brazilian crowd were the latest ugly chapter in Gatlin's saga.\", \"from\": 3247, \"to\": 3327, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The boos\", \"from\": 3247, \"to\": 3255}, {\"ngram\": \"the Brazilian crowd\", \"from\": 3261, \"to\": 3280}, {\"ngram\": \"the latest ugly chapter\", \"from\": 3286, \"to\": 3309}, {\"ngram\": \"Gatlin's saga\", \"from\": 3313, \"to\": 3326}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's been punished for doping twice.\", \"from\": 3328, \"to\": 3364, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His last ban ended in 2010.\", \"from\": 3365, \"to\": 3392, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His last ban\", \"from\": 3365, \"to\": 3377}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But fans in the stadium bought into the \\\"Good vs.\", \"from\": 3393, \"to\": 3442, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 3397, \"to\": 3401}, {\"ngram\": \"the stadium\", \"from\": 3405, \"to\": 3416}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"Good vs.\", \"from\": 3429, \"to\": 3442}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Evil\\\" story line that's been pitched by the media for all these years, and they let the American have it.\", \"from\": 3443, \"to\": 3548, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3531, \"end\": 3539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9986742282922441, \"rank\": 0.0013275315965968716, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Evil\\\" story line\", \"from\": 3443, \"to\": 3459}, {\"ngram\": \"the media\", \"from\": 3483, \"to\": 3492}, {\"ngram\": \"all these years\", \"from\": 3497, \"to\": 3512}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We all have respect for each other,\\\" Gatlin said of himself and his fellow competitors.\", \"from\": 3552, \"to\": 3640, \"entities\": [], \